[goal]
Ship the auth refresh fix to production with minimal regression risk.

[context]
- JWT refresh races the cookie parser on full-page reload.
- Reproduces only on Chrome 121+ with SameSite=Strict.

[constraints]
- Do not change the login UI.
- Preserve existing cookie names.
- Add a regression test before merging.

[notes]
@priority: 2
- Rand mentioned trying a service worker — probably out of scope for this sprint.
- Old workaround in commit 4f3a2d1 might still be useful as a reference.

[rationale]
@priority: 8
- The middleware change affects every authenticated route, so the test plan
  must cover both first-visit and refresh flows. Dropping this section under
  budget pressure would hide the actual reason the reviewer should approve.

